                            <comment id="14704846" author="JIRAUSER20507" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2024 10:00:53 -0700"  >The working directory error message has been correctly occurring by accident. &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8305746&quot; title=&quot;InitializeEncoding should cache Charset object instead of charset name&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8305746&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8305746&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced behavior to cache the Charset object over the Charset name. The fix itself is fine, but the change allows for this exception to be concealed and thus an unexpected exception to occur later down the line. We can restore the expected behavior by ensuring the exception site also returns NULL, as the caller checks for a NULL return value.</comment>
